# How to use this file
# 1) Copy this file and rename it to: .env   (same folder as app.py)
# 2) Put values after the = sign, e.g. REDIS=localhost:6379
# 3) Start the app. It will read these environment variables.
#    (If you also pass a command-line flag, the flag wins.)

# -------------------------
# Secrets. Leave blank if not used.
PUBMED_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=
HTCONDOR_TOKEN=
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=

# -------------------------
# Non-secret settings (optional). You can set them here or via command-line flags.
# HIGH=1
# MEDIUM=1
# LOW=1
# REDIS=localhost:6379 # only change this if you know what you're doing
# API_PORT=8000
# TIMEZONE="America/Chicago"

# -------------------------
# Notes
# - No spaces around '=' (use quotes if a value contains spaces).
# - Do NOT commit your .env file to version control.
